      "writtenOn": "2026-05-28T13:30:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The flags byte is defined NSM spec Table 6-24 (0x10 Set Clock Limit) and it is a bitfield with 2 named flags:\n1. Persistence - the clock limit setting persists across module resets.\n2. Clear - clears the clock limit settings.\n\n`clockLimitFlagClear \u003d 0x03` sets both, which clear the previously set limit and persist that cleared state across module resets, which is what `Reset` semantically means.",
      "parentUuid": "952b50c6_d29600ac",
